-flashing";s:5:"title";s:51:"6 Steps To Program Old Craftsman Garage Door Opener";s:3:"alt";s:29:"window covering manufacturers";s:3:"url";s:48:"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MnReGi0lzO4/hqdefault.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQo0MY17OOUH-0N35Q9EaseyuMySw50ya1rDQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:360;s:6:"height";i:480;s:6:"source";s:72:"https://www.wcmanet.org/how-to-program-old-craftsman-garage-door-opener/";s:6:"domain";s:15:"www.wcmanet.org";}}s:9:"sentences";a:65:{i:0;s:62:"Chamberlain garage door opener troubleshooting blinking light.";i:1;s:190:"The diagnostic code that you are observing Learn button flashing six times indicates that the receiver logic board has detected a motor circuit failure through its self diagnostic circuitry.";i:2;s:90:"The most common reason for the lights to flash on the garage door opener and the door not.";i:3;s:72:"Your garage door opener is programmed with self-diagnostic capabilities.";i:4;s:149:"The diagnostic LED light next to the learn button will flash a number of times then pause before repeating signifying it has found a potential issue.";i:5;s:45:"Why is my garage door opener button flashing.";i:6;s:164:"The most common reason for the lights to flash on the garage door opener and the door not closing is that the safety reversing sensors are misaligned or obstructed.";i:7;s:51:"This is a safety feature of the garage door opener.";i:8;s:57:"What does the flashing LED next to the learn button mean.";i:9;s:64:"Garage Door will not close and the opener lights flash 10 times.";i:10;s:77:"One or both of the LEDs on the safety reversing sensors do not glow steadily.";i:11;s:59:"A broken or disconnected wire to a safety reversing sensor.";i:12;s:197:"The constantly flashing wall button simply means that the door was either put into lock-out mode by someone using the wall panel control or for some reason it defaulted into lock-out mode in error.";i:13;s:147:"When the garage door opener is locked-out the transmitters will be disabled from opening the door but the wall button will still function as usual.";i:14;s:190:"The diagnostic code that you are observing Learn button flashing six times indicates that the receiver logic board has detected a motor circuit failure through its self diagnostic circuitry.";i:15;s:112:"Internal schematics of the receiver logic board are not available to explain further details of this fault code.";i:16;s:79:"Immediately press and hold the LEARN button again until the LEARN LED goes out.";i:17;s:43:"How do I reset my Genie garage door remote.";i:18;s:53:"To reprogram your new andor existing remote controls.";i:19;s:124:"Press and release the learn code button on the receiver while the red LED is blinking press your transmitter button 3 times.";i:20;s:23:"ERASE THE TRANSMITTERS.";i:21;s:136:"Hold down the learn button for 6 or 7 secondsIf you have a MY-Q deviceimmediately press and hold the LEARN button again until the learn.";i:22;s:30:"Random flashing means nothing.";i:23;s:66:"1 FLASH Safety reversing sensors wire open broken or disconnected.";i:24;s:76:"2 FLASHES Safety reversing sensors wire shorted or blackwhite wire reversed.";i:25;s:39:"3 FLASHES Door control or wire shorted.";i:26;s:75:"4 FLASHES Safety reversing sensors slightly misaligned dim or flashing LED.";i:27;s:58:"5 FLASHES Motor overheated or possible RPM sensor failure.";i:28;s:129:"Its important to note that when the lock button is on your garage door opener will only work from the switch located by the door.";i:29;s:33:"The remote control will not work.";i:30;s:69:"To unlock your garage door opener push the lock button for 5 seconds.";i:31;s:79:"Once you push this button the light on the garage door opener will flash twice.";i:32;s:76:"While holding the ENTER button watch the LED light next to the LEARN button.";i:33;s:41:"If it is blinking it is sending a signal.";i:34;s:57:"Press and release the LEARN button and it should program.";i:35;s:64:"If it is not blinking the radio control is not sending a signal.";i:36;s:26:"Check for compatibility a.";i:37;s:165:"If you own a new garage door opener that comes with a locking feature its possible someone may have accidentally locked your garage door by pressing the lock button.";i:38;s:150:"If you try to open your door using a remote while the lock system is engaged youll notice that the garage door light will begin blinking continuously.";i:39;s:83:"The locking feature is meant to prevent garage door remotes from opening your door.";i:40;s:97:"I have a craftsman garage door opener model 13953673SRT built in 1996 w a redorange LEARN button.";i:41;s:68:"It did not come w an outdoor keypad and I decided to go buy one now.";i:42;s:35:"Liftmaster garage door opener mean.";i:43;s:158:"The Chamberlain Liftmaster Craftsman garage door openers have a built-in diagnostic indicator that will assist you in troubleshooting your garage door opener.";i:44;s:134:"There is a LED light next to or near the smart button programming learn button on the outside of the motor cover up above the antenna.";i:45;s:108:"The learn button for your garage door opener is located on the back or side of the garage door opener motor.";i:46;s:85:"The learn button allows you to program compatible remotes to your garage door opener.";i:47;s:87:"You may notice that different garage door openers have different colored learn buttons.";i:48;s:80:"These colors are important as they let you know what frequency your garage door.";i:49;s:111:"Flashing garage door lights are like a Check Engine Light will indicate which part needs to be addressed fixed.";i:50;s:69:"The garage door opener lights will flash or two clicks will be heard.";i:51;s:33:"The remote control is programmed.";i:52;s:48:"To program using your door control LEARN button.";i:53;s:44:"Locate the Learn button on the door control.";i:54;s:29:"Press the Learn button twice.";i:55;s:19:"The LED will blink.";i:56;s:85:"Press and release the button on the remote that you wish to operate your garage door.";i:57;s:18:"Down arrow button.";i:58;s:69:"The garage door opener does not close and the light bulb is flashing.";i:59;s:103:"Safety sensors have been installed connected to the motor or the connecting wires are short or damaged.";i:60;s:46:"Check the wiring and replace any broken wires.";i:61;s:62:"The garage door opener will not close and the light bulb will.";i:62;s:121:"When the lock button is ON the garage door opener will work from the wall control but the remote controls are locked out.";i:63;s:193:"The Safety Reversing Sensors The most common reason for the lights to flash on the garage door opener and the door not closing is that the safety reversing sensors are misaligned or obstructed.";i:64;s:51:"This is a safety feature of the garage door opener.";}}